               <p>WILLIAM BEWS HARRIS. I am a <rs id="t18320906-435-viclabel2450" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-435-victim3516 t18320906-435-viclabel2450"></join> - I live in Forest-row, Dalston. On Saturday night, between eleven and twelve o'clock, I met the prisoner in Bishopsgate-street- I had been drinking, but was in my senses; they accosted me; I went to two public-houses with them, and drank -I had a quartern of rum at the second house - a baker came in, and insulted me; he went away, and at that moment my purse was safe - I had taken it out of my fob in the prisoner's presence, to pay for the liquor; I had a sovereign, half a sovereign, half a crown, and 4s. in it - I went away, and was going home; the prisoners followed me, and came to me again; Johnson was on my left-hand side, and Jones on my right; she left me suddenly -Jones loitered rather behind, and Johnson called her, which excited my suspicion - I felt, and missed my purse from my left-hand pocket; I directly seized Johnson, and said she had robbed me - a Policeman came up; I told him - my bag of money was found concealed on Jones.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-435-person3517">
                  SILVANUS 
